cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper deals with the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial examples in the physical world, specifically in the context of road sign classification. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a general attack algorithm and evaluates the efficacy of physical adversarial manipulations, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of DNNs in safety-critical situations, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
